  { n: 96, s: "English Language", q: "In each question, three words are given in bold, which may or may not be in their correct positions. Choose the correct sequence of words from the given options to make the sentence grammatically correct and meaningful.\n\nA wildlife (A)of an eagle was carved (B)out of wood for the sculpture (C)event.", o: ["BCA", "CBA", "ACB", "BAC", "No rearrangement needed"], a: 1, e: "The correct rearrangement of the highlighted words is CBA.\nThus, the correct sentence will be, “A sculpture of an eagle was carved out of wood for the wildlife event.”", qimg: "", eimg: "" },
  { n: 97, s: "English Language", q: "In each question, three words are given in bold, which may or may not be in their correct positions. Choose the correct sequence of words from the given options to make the sentence grammatically correct and meaningful.\n\nBlood was analyzed (A)through a/an diagnostic (B)machine to figure out whether the patient was suffering (C)from cancer or the flu.", o: ["BCA", "CBA", "ACB", "BAC", "No rearrangement needed"], a: 4, e: "All the highlighted words in the given sentence are correctly placed. Hence, no rearrangement needed.", qimg: "", eimg: "" },
  { n: 98, s: "English Language", q: "In each question, three words are given in bold, which may or may not be in their correct positions. Choose the correct sequence of words from the given options to make the sentence grammatically correct and meaningful.\n\nWithout any solitude (A) a/an crazy (B) is bound to go a bit introvert (C)", o: ["BCA", "CBA", "ACB", "BAC", "No rearrangement needed"], a: 2, e: "The correct rearrangement of the highlighted words is ACB\nThus, the correct sentence will be, “Without any solitude, an introvert is bound to go a bit crazy.”", qimg: "", eimg: "" },
  { n: 99, s: "English Language", q: "In each question, three words are given in bold, which may or may not be in their correct positions. Choose the correct sequence of words from the given options to make the sentence grammatically correct and meaningful.\n\nThe allowed(A) material permeable (B)a large amount of water to seep (C)through.", o: ["BCA", "CBA", "ACB", "BAC", "No rearrangement needed"], a: 3, e: "The correct rearrangement of the highlighted words is BAC\nThus, the correct sentence will be, ‘The permeable material allowed a large amount of water to seep through.”", qimg: "", eimg: "" },
  { n: 100, s: "English Language", q: "In each question, three words are given in bold, which may or may not be in their correct positions. Choose the correct sequence of words from the given options to make the sentence grammatically correct and meaningful.\n\nThe astronomer observation (A)a new star during a/an discover(B) recent(C)", o: ["BCA", "CBA", "ACB", "BAC", "No rearrangement needed"], a: 0, e: "The correct rearrangement of the highlighted words is BCA\nThus, the correct sentence will be, “The astronomer discovered a new star during a recent observation”", qimg: "", eimg: "" }
